If you’re going to argue about the RL—which is a bad premise to begin with—that’s a poor angle of attack. “Wizards made a promise and we want them to stay beholden to their promises” is a better argument. Jimmy and Josh are selling a playmat right now that will *never* be sold again. The appeal is the exclusivity. If they make more in two years, people would be like “yo, what the fuck.” That’s the attitude we should have about the RL. WotC made a promise and we don’t want them to renege on those just like we don’t want content creators to lie to us.
